4 HJR___ NAMING THE BRIDGE ON UNITED STATES HIGHWAY 45 THAT
5 SPANS BENNETT CREEK IN MOBILE COUNTY THE SIDNEY ALDEN HOBBS
6 MEMORIAL BRIDGE.
7
8 WHEREAS, it is with the highest accolade that this
9 body honors the memory of Sidney Alden Hobbs by requesting
10 the Department of Transportation designate the bridge on
11 United States Highway 45 that spans Bennett Creek in Mobile
12 County, Alabama, as the Sidney Alden Hobbs Memorial Bridge;
13 and
14 WHEREAS, Sid Hobbs was born March 24, 2008, to John
15 and Elizabeth Hobbs in Citronelle, Alabama; he was a
16 lifelong member of Living Word Church with his siblings and
17 parents where he was active in his youth group; his faith
18 was evident in his kindhearted demeanor and his love for
19 others; and
20 WHEREAS, Sid lived his life to the fullest and,
21 though many others would have found struggle and defeat, Sid
22 remained positive and motivated throughout his many battles
23 with brain cancer; his bright spirit and loving nature
24 continue to inspire his community; with the naming of this
25 bridge in his honor, his legacy of resilience will be
26 remembered for generations to come; now therefore,
27 BE IT RESOLVED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA, BOTH
28 HOUSES THEREOF CONCURRING, That to honor Sidney Alden Hobbs,
Page 1

HOUSES THEREOF CONCURRING, That to honor Sidney Alden Hobbs,
HJR133 INTRODUCED
29 who loved his community and was beloved in return, the
30 Department of Transportation is encouraged to coordinate
31 with local governing officials to consider designating the
32 bridge on United States Highway 45 that spans Bennett Creek
33 in Mobile County the Sidney Alden Hobbs Memorial Bridge and
34 to erect appropriate signs or markers, consistent with
35 applicable requirements and laws, in recognition of this
36 designation.
